  "prompt": "What are some good auto biographies?",
  "response": "There are many compelling autobiographies across various genres and subjects. Here are some highly regarded ones:\n\n1. **\"The Diary of a Young Girl\" by Anne Frank** - The poignant diary of a Jewish girl hiding from the Nazis during World War II.\n\n2. **\"Becoming\" by Michelle Obama** - The former First Lady shares her life story, focusing on her roots, public role, and the challenges she faced.\n\n3. **\"Long Walk to Freedom\" by Nelson Mandela** - Mandela recounts his early life, struggle against apartheid, and years in prison.\n\n4. **\"The Autobiography of Malcolm X\" as told to Alex Haley** - A powerful account of the life and beliefs of the civil rights leader.\n\n5. **\"Educated\" by Tara Westover** - A memoir about a woman who grows up in a strict and abusive household in rural Idaho but ultimately escapes to learn about the world through education.\n\n6. **\"Steve Jobs\" by Walter Isaacson** - While technically a biography, it includes extensive interviews with Jobs, providing insight into his life and philosophy.\n\n7. **\"I Know Why the Caged Bird Sings\" by Maya Angelou** - A powerful narrative about the author's early years and the impact of racism and abuse on her life.\n\n8. **\"When Breath Becomes Air\" by Paul Kalanithi** - A moving exploration of mortality from the perspective of a neurosurgeon diagnosed with terminal cancer.\n\n9. **\"The Glass Castle\" by Jeannette Walls** - A memoir about the author\u2019s unconventional and often challenging upbringing by her eccentric parents.\n\n10. **\"Born a Crime\" by Trevor Noah** - A humorous yet poignant account of the comedian's childhood in South Africa during apartheid.\n\nEach of these autobiographies offers unique insights into different lives, cultures, and experiences, making them worth reading.",
